# Workspace scope — REIT Assistant only

**Effective immediately.** The agent/build bot must NOT use full-system or root-level access.

## Allowed scope

- **Only** `/Users/nancyfletcher/Documents/reit-assistant-fqe` and its subdirectories
- All reads, writes, edits, deletes, and terminal `cwd` must stay within this tree

## Blocked (do not access or modify)

- System folders (`/System`, `/usr`, `/etc`, `/var`, etc.)
- User home outside this project (`~` except paths under `reit-assistant-fqe`)
- Unrelated projects (e.g. other repos under `~/Documents/`)
- `deliverables/` mockups/prototype (design reference is in `docs/` only)
- Global git config, global npm config, or machine-wide installs unless the user explicitly overrides in chat

## Shell commands

- Set `working_directory` to the project root or a subdirectory
- Do not run commands that write outside the project (e.g. `cp` to `~/Downloads`, `rm -rf` outside scope)
- Prefer project-relative paths only

## If a task requires out-of-scope access

- Stop and tell the user what is needed and why
- Do not proceed without explicit approval
